British Columbia is the westernmost province of Canada, situated between the Pacific Ocean and the Rocky Mountains.

It has a diverse geography, with rugged landscapes that include rocky coastlines, sandy beaches, forests, lakes, mountains, inland deserts and grassy plains, and borders the province of Alberta to the east and the Yukon and Northwest Territories to the north.

With an estimated population of 5.3 million as of 2022, it is Canada's third-most populous province.

The capital of British Columbia is Victoria and its largest city is Vancouver. Vancouver is the third-largest metropolitan area in Canada.
